// Local Government Act 1976 [Act 171] — the local-council (PBT) enforcement
// cluster: s75 (entry to inspect/cleanse houses — s75(3): NO entry into an
// occupied dwelling-house without SIX HOURS' notice or consent), s102 (general
// by-law-making power — grounds "yes, the council genuinely can regulate this"),
// s104 (by-law breach penalty ceiling: RM2,000 / 1 year), s107 (licences +
// conditions + revocation), s110 (entry to premises at reasonable times),
// s111 (occupier must give name/IC on demand), s112 (obstructing council
// officers), s121 (arrest — council officer or police may arrest WITHOUT
// warrant ONLY if name/address unknown+declined or doubted; must reach a
// Magistrate within 24 hours).
// AUTHORITY: introduces authority:"PBT" (Pihak Berkuasa Tempatan — local
// authorities: city halls / municipal / district councils). DBKL is the FT KL
// instance: constituted under the Federal Capital Act 1960 [Act 190]
// (raw/act190/), with this Act applying to the FT via Minister's gazette
// (s1(3)); s112 names the Commissioner of the City of Kuala Lumpur directly.
// s121 also empowers police — single-authority field limitation again (tagged
// PBT as the primary enforcing body; same caveat as rta1987 JPJ note).
// SCOPE: s1(1) — Peninsular Malaysia only (state:"PENINSULAR"); Sabah/Sarawak
// have their own local-government ordinances — fail-soft there.
// GAP: the by-laws themselves (vandalism, hawker, parking by-laws etc.) are
// subsidiary legislation NOT on the AGC portal — this Act grounds the powers
// and penalty ceilings, not the individual by-law texts. Never quote a by-law
// from memory.
// EN text pdftotext-extracted from the official AGC "online version of updated
// text of reprint — as at 1 December 2012" (corpus/raw/act171/en.pdf). BM
// official text exists (raw/act171/bm.pdf, same as-at) — BM chunks deferred.
// All chunks verified:false until a human word-for-word PDF check.
{"id": "LGA1976-s75-en-0", "authority": "PBT", "statute": "Local Government Act 1976", "statute_abbr": "LGA 1976", "act_number": "171", "state": "PENINSULAR", "section": "75", "heading": "Power to enter and cleanse houses or buildings", "lang": "en", "text": "75. (1) The Health Officer, or any officer authorized by the local authority in that behalf in writing, may at any time enter and inspect all houses and buildings and by an order in writing direct the occupier to cause within a time to be specified in such order all or any part thereof to be internally and externally colour-washed or distempered or otherwise cleansed for sanitary reasons and if necessary disinfected and all dirt or rubbish to be removed or collected.\n(2) If such order is not complied with within the time specified, the occupier shall be guilty of an offence and shall on conviction be liable to a fine not exceeding one thousand ringgit or to a term of imprisonment not exceeding six months or to both such fine and imprisonment and to a further fine not exceeding one hundred ringgit for each day after conviction until the order is complied with.\n(3) No entry shall be made into any dwelling-house in actual occupation, not being a common lodging-house, without six hours’ previous notice to the occupier unless with his consent.", "source_url": "https://lom.agc.gov.my/act-detail.php?language=BI&act=171", "as_at": "2012-12-01", "verified": false}
{"id": "LGA1976-s102-en-0", "authority": "PBT", "statute": "Local Government Act 1976", "statute_abbr": "LGA 1976", "act_number": "171", "state": "PENINSULAR", "section": "102", "heading": "General power to make by-laws", "lang": "en", "text": "102. In addition to the powers of making by-laws expressly or impliedly conferred upon it by any other provisions of this Act every local authority may from time to time make, amend and revoke by-laws in respect of all such matters as are necessary or desirable for the maintenance of the health, safety and well-being of the inhabitants or for the good order and government of the local authority area and in particular in respect of all or any of the following purposes:\n(a) to regulate the form in which all estimates, budgets, statements, returns, or other accounts of the local authority shall be drawn up and kept;\n(b) to regulate the repairing, cleaning, watering and lighting of streets, roads, canals and bridges;\n(c) to regulate, license, restrict, prevent or remove the exhibition of advertisements;\n(d) to regulate the planting, preservation and removal of trees, flowers and shrubs in public places;\n(e) to provide for the protection from damage or interference of any local authority works or property situated or being in, under or over any public or private place within the local authority area;\n(f) to provide for the establishment, regulation and management of any public park, walk, recreation and pleasure ground, garden, swimming pool, lake, stadium, historical building or site, public library, art gallery, museum, public theatre, restaurant, hall, assembly room, botanical or zoological garden or aquarium;\n(g) to regulate within the local authority area the landing and temporary storage of goods upon public quays, wharves and streets, adjacent to any port, or any waterway connected therewith, and to fix the fees to be charged in respect of such temporary storage;\n(h) to regulate any public sales held in any public place;\n(i) to define the streets or areas within which shops, warehouses, factories or business premises may not be erected, or within which specified trades, businesses or callings may not be established or carried on;\n(j) to regulate, license, supervise, restrict or prohibit the playing of musical instruments, singing or performing for profit, in any public place;\n(k) to regulate the maintenance, distribution and use of any artificial light, gas or other energy that is supplied by the local authority;\n(l) to provide for the establishment, maintenance, regulation and control of public transport services and to prescribe fares to be charged;\n(m) to regulate fire brigades and to provide for the conditions of service, administration and discipline of all members thereof;\n(n) (i) to regulate, supervise and license trishaws and carts and to prescribe the rates or fares, whether by distance or time within or without the local authority area to be charged for such services, the number of passengers and the weights, dimensions, and nature of the loads to be carried and the mode of construction thereof; (ii) to prescribe standards of medical and physical fitness and efficiency for the riders, drivers or haulers of trishaws or carts, as the case may be;\n(o) to provide for the licensing of bicycles and tricycles;\n(p) to provide for the establishment, regulation, inspection and licensing of places of entertainment, public recreation or public resort, and to make regulations governing the means of ingress to and egress from such places and for providing adequate parking space adjacent or in reasonable proximity thereto;\n(q) to prohibit, restrict or regulate the transportation and quarrying of stone, lime, clay, sand or other material on any premises and the burning of lime and manufacture of bricks;\n(r) to prohibit, restrict or regulate the use of any land as a pond for the keeping or breeding of fish;\n(s) to control and supervise, by registration, licensing or otherwise, including in proper cases by prohibition, a trade, business or industry which is of an obnoxious nature or which could be a source of nuisance to the public or a class of the public;\n(t) to provide for the offences under this Act and any by-laws which may be compounded by the local authority, the persons who may compound, the limit of the sum of money to be collected by such local authority for compounding such offences and the procedure and forms to be complied with in compounding; and (u) in so far as they do not fall within any of the preceding paragraphs, to provide for all procedural and other matters which by this Act are required or permitted to be prescribed, or which are necessary or convenient to be prescribed for carrying out or giving effect to the provisions of this Act.\nBy-law, etc., may prescribe fees and charges 102A. Any by-law, rule or regulation made by a local authority may prescribe fees and charges for any matter or thing required or authorized to be done thereunder.", "source_url": "https://lom.agc.gov.my/act-detail.php?language=BI&act=171", "as_at": "2012-12-01", "verified": false}
{"id": "LGA1976-s104-en-0", "authority": "PBT", "statute": "Local Government Act 1976", "statute_abbr": "LGA 1976", "act_number": "171", "state": "PENINSULAR", "section": "104", "heading": "Penalties for breaches of by-laws", "lang": "en", "text": "104. A local authority may, by by-law, rule or regulation prescribe for the breach of any by-law, rule or regulation a fine not exceeding two thousand ringgit or a term of imprisonment not exceeding one year or to both and in the case of a continuing offence a sum not exceeding two hundred ringgit for each day during which such offence is continued after conviction.", "source_url": "https://lom.agc.gov.my/act-detail.php?language=BI&act=171", "as_at": "2012-12-01", "verified": false}
{"id": "LGA1976-s107-en-0", "authority": "PBT", "statute": "Local Government Act 1976", "statute_abbr": "LGA 1976", "act_number": "171", "state": "PENINSULAR", "section": "107", "heading": "Licences", "lang": "en", "text": "107. (1) A local authority in the granting of any licence or permit may prescribe the fees for such licence or permit and the charges for the inspection or supervision of any trade, occupation or premises in respect of which the licence is granted. (1A) Any licence or permit granted under this Act may be issued jointly with any other licence or permit.\n(2) Every licence or permit granted shall be subject to such conditions and restrictions as the local authority may think fit and shall be revocable by the local authority at any time without assigning any reason therefor. (2A) The revocation of any particular licence or permit issued jointly with any other licence or permit under subsection (1A) shall not affect the validity of any other licence or permit with which it had been jointly issued.\n(3) The local authority may at its discretion refuse to grant or renew any licence without assigning any reason therefor.\n(4) A licence shall be valid for a period not exceeding three years.\n(5) Every person to whom a licence has been granted shall exhibit his licence at all times in some prominent place on the licensed premises and shall produce such licence if required to do so by any officer of the local authority authorized to demand the same.\n(6) Any person who fails to exhibit or to produce such licence under subsection (5) shall be guilty of an offence and shall on conviction be liable to a fine not exceeding five hundred ringgit or to imprisonment for a term not exceeding six months or to both.\n(7) For the purpose of subsection (5) or (6) any reference to the word “licence” shall include its certified true copy.\n(8) The certification of any licence as a true copy shall be made by the President, Secretary or any officer authorized by the President in writing.", "source_url": "https://lom.agc.gov.my/act-detail.php?language=BI&act=171", "as_at": "2012-12-01", "verified": false}
{"id": "LGA1976-s110-en-0", "authority": "PBT", "statute": "Local Government Act 1976", "statute_abbr": "LGA 1976", "act_number": "171", "state": "PENINSULAR", "section": "110", "heading": "Power to enter premises", "lang": "en", "text": "110. Any officer of a local authority duly authorized in writing may at all reasonable times, enter any premises within the local authority area for the purpose of exercising any power of inspection, enquiry or execution of works which is given to a local authority.", "source_url": "https://lom.agc.gov.my/act-detail.php?language=BI&act=171", "as_at": "2012-12-01", "verified": false}
{"id": "LGA1976-s111-en-0", "authority": "PBT", "statute": "Local Government Act 1976", "statute_abbr": "LGA 1976", "act_number": "171", "state": "PENINSULAR", "section": "111", "heading": "Officer may demand names and addresses", "lang": "en", "text": "111. (1) The occupier of any premises within the local authority area shall, if required by any officer of a local authority, give his name and identity card number and the name and address of the owner of the premises, if known.\n(2) Any person who refuses to give or wilfully misstates his name and identity card number or the name and address of the owner of the premises shall be guilty of an offence and shall on conviction be liable to a fine not exceeding five hundred ringgit or to a term of imprisonment not exceeding six months or to both.", "source_url": "https://lom.agc.gov.my/act-detail.php?language=BI&act=171", "as_at": "2012-12-01", "verified": false}
{"id": "LGA1976-s112-en-0", "authority": "PBT", "statute": "Local Government Act 1976", "statute_abbr": "LGA 1976", "act_number": "171", "state": "PENINSULAR", "section": "112", "heading": "Penalty for obstructing Councillor and others", "lang": "en", "text": "112. Any person who at any time obstructs, molests or assaults the Commissioner of the City of Kuala Lumpur, or the Mayor or President, Councillors, officers or employees of a local authority in the performance and execution of their duty or removes any mark set up for the purpose of indicating any level or direction necessary to the execution of works shall be guilty of an offence and shall on conviction be liable to a fine not exceeding two thousand ringgit or to a term of imprisonment not exceeding six months or to both.", "source_url": "https://lom.agc.gov.my/act-detail.php?language=BI&act=171", "as_at": "2012-12-01", "verified": false}
{"id": "LGA1976-s121-en-0", "authority": "PBT", "statute": "Local Government Act 1976", "statute_abbr": "LGA 1976", "act_number": "171", "state": "PENINSULAR", "section": "121", "heading": "Power of arrest", "lang": "en", "text": "121. (1) Any officer of the local authority authorized by the local authority or any police officer may arrest without warrant any person who commits in his presence or whom he reasonably believes to have committed any offence under this Act or any bylaw, rule or regulation—\n(a) if the name or address of the person is unknown to him and the person declines to give his name and address; or (b) if there is reason to doubt the accuracy of the name or address.\n(2) A person arrested under this section shall be detained and shall be brought before a Magistrate’s Court within twenty-four hours unless his name and address are sooner ascertained.", "source_url": "https://lom.agc.gov.my/act-detail.php?language=BI&act=171", "as_at": "2012-12-01", "verified": false}
